              {
                "dsDescriptionValue": {
                  "typeName": "dsDescriptionValue",
                  "typeClass": "primitive",
                  "multiple": false,
                  "value": "A tidy, documented, reproducible dataset of Colorado stream/river flow (daily mean discharge, cubic feet per second) at major-river gages, liberated from two public sources (USGS NWIS and Colorado DWR/CDSS surface water) into a single long-format CSV: one row per (source, site_id, datetime, variable). Each gage carries its full period of record (many to the early 1900s). Part of the Colorado Environmental Data Hub (CUPIDS Lab); implements issue #10. Note that the two sources OVERLAP — DWR re-serves many USGS gages (joinable via usgs_site_no) — and must be de-duplicated to one series per gage for analysis; the overlap doubles as a built-in cross-source accuracy check. Each extract carries per-source provenance (source URL, retrieval time, SHA-256, license). Regenerated and re-audited monthly from the source APIs; see the repository for the re-runnable pipeline."
                }
              }
            ]
          },
